ðŸ”¥ FLAMES Game Web AppAn interactive web-based version of the popular FLAMES game, built entirely in Python using the Streamlit framework.ðŸ› ï¸ FeaturesDynamic Input: Accepts two names and automatically processes them for character matching.Efficient Algorithm: Uses list slicing and modulo arithmetic to accurately simulate the circular elimination of the letters F-L-A-M-E-S.Clean UI: A minimalist dark-themed interface with real-time feedback.ðŸš€ How to RunClone the repository:Bashgit clone https://github.com/yourusername/flames-streamlit.git
Install requirements:
Bashpip install streamlit
Launch the app:
Bashstreamlit run flamesgame.py
ðŸ“œ Game LogicThe app follows the traditional rules:
Removes common characters between the two names.
Calculates the remaining count ($n$).
Iteratively eliminates letters from "FLAMES" using the count $n$ until only one remains.
HERE IT IS THE CODE:
import streamlit as st
st.title("ðŸ”¥ FLAMES Game")
a_input = st.text_input("enter first name")
b_input = st.text_input("enter Second name")

if st.button("get results"):
    if a_input and b_input:
        
        a = list(a_input.lower().replace(" ", ""))
        b = list(b_input.lower().replace(" ", ""))

      
        for i in a[:]: 
            if i in b:
                a.remove(i)
                b.remove(i)

        n = len(a + b)
        s = ["f", "l", "a", "m", "e", "s"]

     
        while len(s) > 1:
            split_index = (n % len(s)) - 1
            if split_index >= 0:
                s = s[split_index + 1:] + s[:split_index]
            else:
                s.pop()

        d = {
            'f':'Friends',
            'l':'Lovers',
            'a':'Affection',
            'm':'Marriage',
            'e':'Enemies',
            's':'Siblings'
        }
        
      
        st.success(f"The result is: **{d[s[0]]}**")
    else:
        st.error("Please enter both names first!")
